  "texts": [
    "Many green bonds incorporate clauses that restrict funding usage to green projects, as issuing these bonds requires auditing for proper utilization; however, the absence of specific usage limitations in general green bonds might increase the risk of greenwashing.",
    "Thus, to explore this possibility, we create a dummy variable that indicates whether the green bond has strict green project recognition clauses for regulating the use of fundraising funds.",
    "The specific model is as follows:",
    "where Clause i,t represents whether green bond i has strict green project recognition clauses in time t. If the green bond has the green project recognition clauses, the value is 1; otherwise, the value is 0.",
    "The definitions of other variables are consistent with the previous text."
  ],
